messages.content: ComfyUI_String_Function_Tree is a custom node for ComfyUI that was modded from the original String Function in ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts to allow plugging more stuff into the original function.
What are the steps to install the original ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts?

To install the original ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts, open a terminal or command line interface, navigate to the `ComfyUI/custom_nodes/` directory, and run the command `git clone https://github.com/pythongosssss/ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts.git`.
What is the command to install the customized version?
To install the customized version of ComfyUI_String_Function_Tree, run the command `git clone https://github.com/wolfden/ComfyUi_String_Function_Tree.git`.
How do I access the new node in ComfyUI after installation?
After restarting ComfyUI, you will find a new menu under the utils submenu called String Function Tree. Clicking on it will add a new node to your workflow.
